Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.60,0:00:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles Darwin is probably the most famous biologist of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.73,0:00:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This museum opened in 1860, just a year after Darwin published the book that would make him famous
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.61,0:00:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>On the Origin of Species</i>.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.09,0:00:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In it, he described how a completely natural process
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.94,0:00:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a process he called "natural selection"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.85,0:00:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,could shape life on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.61,0:00:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and through gradual change, produce millions of different species.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.36,0:00:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin wasn't the only biologist thinking and writing about evolution in the 19th century
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.81,0:00:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but he described how evolution could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.18,0:00:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was a real breakthrough.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He also wrote for a general audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.13,0:00:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>On the Origin of Species</i> wasn't a book written to be read by scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.54,0:00:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a popular science book.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.54,0:00:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so widely read that Darwin quickly became world famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.41,0:00:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,
